# Pacvue Form Template test

Apply these rules to ALL form fields across every create/edit page.

## Field Anatomy

```
[Label — 14px/500/Inter]              ← optional: * for required, gray "(optional)" suffix
[Input / Select / Custom Control]     ← height 36px, see variants below
[Helper text or Error message]        ← 12px, conditional
```

- Label ↔ Field gap: `4px`
- Field ↔ Next-field gap: `16px`
- Section ↔ Section gap: `24px`

---

## Input Variants

### Text Input

```
height: 36px
padding: 8px 12px
border: 1px solid #DEDFE3
border-radius: 4px
font: Inter Regular 14px / #45464f
placeholder color: #B2B2B8
focus: border-color var(--pcv-brand), no box-shadow fill
```

### Dropdown / Select (single)

```
height: 36px
padding: 8px 12px
border: 1px solid #DEDFE3
border-radius: 4px          ← same as text input
font: Inter Regular 14px / #66666c (selected value or placeholder color)
placeholder color: #66666c

Right icon: Pacvue dropdown arrow icon
  - Size: 20 × 20px
  - Icon: "top bar-arrow-down" from Pacvue Icon Library
  - Position: absolute right 12px, vertically centered
  - Color: #DEDFE3 (default) / var(--pcv-brand) (active/open)
  - DO NOT use browser-native <select> arrow or CSS border-triangle
```

### Multi-select

使用普通 Select 下拉，不使用标签式 tag-input，除非 PRD 明确要求多选标签展示。

---

## Dropdown Arrow Icon

Pacvue uses a custom icon, NOT the browser's native `<select>` arrow, and NOT a CSS `border-triangle`.

Until the Pacvue icon SVG is formally provided, render the arrow as:

```html
<!-- Pacvue dropdown arrow (placeholder SVG — replace with official icon) -->
<svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
  <path d="M5 7.5L10 12.5L15 7.5" stroke="#DEDFE3" stroke-width="1.5"
        stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
</svg>
```

**Position**: absolute right `12px`, vertically centered inside the field.

---

## Required & Optional Labels

```
Required:  <span style="color: #EA5455">*</span> FieldName   ← asterisk BEFORE name
Optional:  FieldName <span style="color:#82858B; font-weight:400">(optional)</span>
```

---

## Validation States

| State | Border | Message | Color |
|-------|--------|---------|-------|
| Default | `#DEDFE3` | — | — |
| Focus | `var(--pcv-brand)` | — | — |
| Error | `#EA5455` | Inline below field, 12px | `#EA5455` |
| Disabled | `#EDEEF1` | — | bg `#F6F7FB`, text `#B2B2B8` |
| Read-only | `#EDEEF1` | "Read-only after creation" hint | bg `#F6F7FB`, lock icon right |

---

## Read-Only Field Rules

- `background: #F6F7FB`
- `border: 1px solid #EDEEF1`
- `color: #66666c`
- Lock icon (16×16) on the right inside the field
- `cursor: not-allowed`
- `tabindex="-1"` — cannot receive keyboard focus
- Hover tooltip: explain WHY field is locked

---

## Two-Column Field Grid

When placing two fields side by side:

```css
display: grid;
grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
gap: 16px;
```

Only use 2-column layout for related short fields (e.g. Language + Currency).
Never put unrelated long fields side-by-side.

